Wagyu burger. Insanely good!
Brisket, wagyu burger, buffalo wings, cocktails and beer. All meat is organic, grass fed, hormone free and melts in your mouth...completely falls off the bone. Come hungry!!
Pork chop + fried rice with egg! So good we had to take a bite before the pic.

Wrap up the bbq inside a lettuce wrap! Amazing!
Classic Korean bbq and their KFC boneless chicken crisps.
Satay stalls #7-8! Classic Indian + Costa Rican. Delish!
Coconut sorbet, vanilla gelato with molten lava chocolate cake. Cozy, boho chic atmosphere. Love this place!
You will queue. Worth the wait. Limit is 12 pp. Eat them once they have cooled down and been refrigerated - like cheesecake 2.0. Great for entertaining or an office treat for colleagues! Bon appetit!

tip.text: Everything pictured - amazing + hot sake!
Get the spicy tonkotsu! Trust me!
Chili crab steamed bun, pork dumpling, crab and pork dumpling, pork chop with fried rice. Be prepared to queue 20 min - dont worry, its worth it!
Authentic Shanghai/HK style dimsum. Value + fast service. Xiao Long Bao, liu sar pau, spicy chili oil dumpling, pork + onion dumpling, fried pork chop, mee sua kueh, egg custard bao, etc!
Coco Shake Shack stall (across from famous Tian Tian Hianese chicken rice) - coconut shake (pictured) or Thai tea. Best way to cool off + stay hydrated. Warning: addictive! I crave them daily!
Tian Tian Hianese Chicken Rice. Get the sauces too! There will be a longggg queue...be prepared. Order a Coconut or Thai tea shake from "Coco Shake Shack" just across - will cool you down.
Hong Kee Beef Noodle - recipient of Michelin Bib Gourmand 2016 award. Get extra chili - make it spicy! Delicious!! Try to come before 1 or 1:30 - all the best stalls sell out by then!!

formattedAddress: 7 Maxwell Rd (Telok Ayer St / Amoy St)

tip.text: Try Noodle Story / Authentic Thai (pictured - everything they make is incredible - Thai cook!) or Hong Kee Beef Noodle. Make sure u save a seat w a pack of tissues-it can get packed. Prepare to queue!

tip.text: Incredible gelato! Try the strawberry! Mille grazie!
Imperial seafood (chili crab is legit) just won a Michelin Bib Gourmand award. The chicken wings from 2 stalls next to it - delish! Bring wipes - it will get messy w all this finger food!
Best Satay stall in action!
Best Satay stall 8-9 (outside/front) - peanut sauce + prawn, chicken and beef satay skewers. Bring wipes! It will get messy!
Best Satay stalls 8-9 (ask for peanut sauce). Classic Indian - authentic and delish, try butter chicken + naan + biryani rice + spicy spinach! Make sure to bring wet wipes or tissues!
Best satay, stall 8-9. Classic Indian stall inside - everything is authentic and delish, try biryani rice + butter chicken + spicy spinach!
Amazing Mediterranean-American breakfast with a sea view.
A super cozy and chill boho chic, beach bum meets Mexican pueblo atmosphere!
Make a reservation - get the Omakase menu (chef's choice) - step out of the box and be adventurous. Let Itamae Antonis guide you. You'll thank me later!!
Seared sea bass with caramelized miso - melts in your mouth. Chirasidon. Christopsaro sashimi. Uni/axinos. And barbounia sashimi. Hot sake. Kanpai!
The main ingredients are lacking in quality lately - mushy tomatoes are a turn off. Otherwise, nice sauces. Decent patty. Bun should be brioche though!  - a New Yorker and True Burgermeister
Ari Gold burger. Fries w: cheddar cheese. Get bbq sauce on side (overpowering). If there's a wait, simply go next door to the bar - have a beer. They will call you when your table is ready!
Breakfast Crepes! Bon appetit!
Fresh, homemade gourmet bagels named after EU cities, with the ingredients reflecting each respective region! Delicieux! Try the cheesecake, brownies and cookies! Bon appetit!
Order the spicy Feyrouz laxmatzoun with everything. You're welcome. Kali orexi!
